# 📦 Linux Package Management Cheat Sheet (RedHat vs Ubuntu)

This cheat sheet compares common package management commands for:

- **RedHat / CentOS / Fedora** → `yum` / `dnf`
- **Ubuntu / Debian** → `apt`

---

## 🔄 Update & Upgrade

| Task | RedHat (YUM/DNF) | Ubuntu (APT) | Options | Example |
|------|------------------|--------------|---------|---------|
| Update package index | `dnf makecache` | `apt update` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt update` |
| Upgrade all packages | `dnf upgrade` | `apt upgrade` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt upgrade -y` |
| Full distribution upgrade | `dnf upgrade --refresh` | `apt full-upgrade` | `--refresh` → refresh cache | `sudo apt full-upgrade -y` |

---

## 📥 Install & Reinstall

| Task | RedHat (YUM/DNF) | Ubuntu (APT) | Options | Example |
|------|------------------|--------------|---------|---------|
| Install a package | `dnf install pkg` | `apt install pkg` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt install nginx -y` |
| Reinstall a package | `dnf reinstall pkg` | `apt reinstall pkg` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt reinstall curl` |
| Install from file | `rpm -ivh file.rpm` | `dpkg -i file.deb` | `-i` → install <br>`-v` → verbose <br>`-h` → progress | `sudo dpkg -i file.deb` |

---

## ❌ Remove Packages

| Task | RedHat (YUM/DNF) | Ubuntu (APT) | Options | Example |
|------|------------------|--------------|---------|---------|
| Remove a package | `dnf remove pkg` | `apt remove pkg` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt remove nginx -y` |
| Remove package + config | `dnf remove pkg` | `apt purge pkg` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt purge nginx -y` |
| Remove unused deps | `dnf autoremove` | `apt autoremove` | `-y` → auto confirm | `sudo apt autoremove -y` |

---

## 🔍 Search & Info

| Task | RedHat (YUM/DNF) | Ubuntu (APT) | Options | Example |
|------|------------------|--------------|---------|---------|
| Search for a package | `dnf search pkg` | `apt search pkg` | `--showduplicates` (dnf) | `apt search apache2` |
| Show package info | `dnf info pkg` | `apt show pkg` | — | `apt show curl` |
| List installed packages | `dnf list installed` | `dpkg -l` | `| grep` → filter results | `dpkg -l \| grep nginx` |

---

## 📂 File & Ownership

| Task | RedHat | Ubuntu | Example |
|------|--------|--------|---------|
| List files in package | `rpm -ql pkg` | `dpkg -L pkg` | `dpkg -L apache2` |
| Find which package owns a file | `rpm -qf /path/file` | `dpkg -S /path/file` | `dpkg -S /bin/ls` |

---

## 🧹 Cleanup & Fix

| Task | RedHat (YUM/DNF) | Ubuntu (APT) | Options | Example |
|------|------------------|--------------|---------|---------|
| Clean cache | `dnf clean all` | `apt clean` / `apt autoclean` | `all` → remove everything | `sudo apt clean` |
| Check/Fix broken deps | `dnf check` | `apt --fix-broken install` | `--fix-broken` → repair | `sudo apt --fix-broken install` |

---

## 📑 Repositories

| Task | RedHat | Ubuntu | Example |
|------|--------|--------|---------|
| List repos | `dnf repolist` | `ls /etc/apt/sources.list.d/` | `cat /etc/apt/sources.list` |

---

## ⚡ Notes

- On **RHEL 8+**, `yum` is just a symlink to `dnf`.  
- On **Ubuntu/Debian**, `apt` is for users, `apt-get` is more script-friendly.  
- Always add `-y` in automation to skip prompts.  
